# Cache policy for the static site (served by Hostinger LiteSpeed).
#
# Background: by default the server was sending `Cache-Control: public,
# max-age=604800` (seven days) on every JS/CSS, which meant returning
# visitors kept running stale viewer code for up to a week after a deploy.
# A user who had visited /case/ before the R2 unification couldn't load
# new R2-only cases until they cleared their cache or opened an incognito
# tab. This file fixes that.
#
# Strategy:
#   - HTML / JS / CSS: `no-cache` — browsers may store the response but
#     must revalidate with the server before each use. With the server's
#     existing ETag + Last-Modified, revalidation usually returns 304
#     (no body), so the bandwidth cost is negligible while deploys land
#     immediately.
#   - Images / fonts / SVGs / GLBs: untouched. They rarely change and the
#     default 7-day cache is fine.
<IfModule mod_headers.c>
  <FilesMatch "\.(html|htm|js|css)$">
    Header set Cache-Control "no-cache, must-revalidate"
    Header unset Expires
    Header unset Pragma
  </FilesMatch>
</IfModule>
